HEADWORD: Gelsemine
<hw>Gel"se*mine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An alkaloid obtained from the yellow jasmine (<spn>Gelsemium
sempervirens</spn>), as a bitter white semicrystalline substance; --
called also <altname>gelsemia</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gelseminic</ent>⟦br⟧
